    p This statement discloses the privacy practices of Sitevalley.com. By using Sitevalley.com or by agreeing to the Terms and Conditions in Sitevalley.com's Terms of Service, you consent and agree, without limitation or qualification, to the collection, use and disclosure of personal information and to the best privacy practices set out in the Privacy Policy and to any other privacy or data collection policy which is displayed or is included as a link in any individual Sitevalley.com web site. The following is a list of our current Privacy Policy items. We suggest you check back from time-to-time, to see what has been updated.

    .policy__content
        .policy__block#policy1
            .fz-h3 Transmission of Personal Data
            p When you order from Sitevalley.com, all your personal information is protected. We use Secure Sockets Layer (SSL), the industry standard, for encrypting all personal information, including name, address and credit card numbers.
        .policy__block#policy2
            .fz-h3 Cookies and Web Beacons
            p Nowadays, cookies are used on most major web sites. Most browsers are initially set up to accept cookies. If you prefer, you can reset your browser either to notify you when you have received a cookie, or to refuse to accept cookies. You should understand that while Sitevalley.com does not require you to use cookies, certain pages may not function properly if you set your browser to not accept cookies. A cookie is a small text file containing a unique identification number that is transferred from a web site to the hard drive of your computer so that the web site may identify you. This unique number identifies your browser, but not you, to Sitevalley.com's servers whenever you visit Sitevalley.com. A cookie will not let a web site know any personal information about you, such as your real name and address. The coding in the cookies lets us know that you are using a particular computer but nothing more. Since cookies are only text files, they cannot run on your computer, search your computer for other information or transmit any information to anyone.

        .policy__block#policy3
            .fz-h3 To help serve you better, Sitevalley.com uses cookies to:
            p Help us remember who you are through your browser settings so that we can offer and provide personalized services. Sitevalley.com uses cookies to store and sometimes track information about what is done and seen across Sitevalley.com. Cookies also allow us to save passwords and preferences for you so that you will not have to re-enter them the next time you visit.
            p Measure traffic patterns. Without cookies, it could be difficult for us to know that certain services are more popular than others are. This information helps us to better understand when to offer new services.
            p Estimate audience size. Cookies help us know whether or not users have seen particular displays, including advertisements. Displaying advertisements. Sitevalley.com and third party advertising networks used by Sitevalley.com may use cookies when serving advertisements.

        .policy__block#policy4
            .fz-h3 How does Sitevalley.com use the information

            p Any personal information you provide to Sitevalley.com is maintained and accessible only by Sitevalley.com, unless specifically stated otherwise. Sitevalley.com requests information from its users so that users can enjoy customized experiences across Sitevalley.com. We may use the information collected as follows:

            p To offer users the ability to customize or personalize content.

            p To deliver products and services requested.

            p Sitevalley.com uses the anonymous, aggregate data collected to inform our sponsors and advertisers as to numbers of people who have certain demographic characteristics and the number of those people who have seen and "clicked" on their advertisement(s). Sitevalley.com will also disclose to those third-party sponsors and advertisers the overall demographics available regarding who saw and "clicked" on their advertisement. No personal information will be disclosed to these sponsors and advertisers as part of this process; only information in an anonymous, aggregate form will be disclosed.

            p Sitevalley.com also uses the anonymous, aggregate data to perform statistical analyses of the collective characteristics and behavior of our registered users and visitors, to measure user demographics and interests regarding specific areas of Sitevalley.com, to describe our services to third parties such as prospective business partners and advertisers and to analyze how and where best to use our resources. Without such data, we would not know what the most popular areas of Sitevalley.com are, and we would not be able to change and update the content and services appropriately. Sitevalley.com also uses such data to monitor and improve the operation of Sitevalley.com and to maintain the quality of the Products and Services made available through Sitevalley.com. No personal information will be disclosed during these activities.
            p Sitevalley.com may, from time to time, use your personal information to contact you about changes or enhancements to Products and Services on Sitevalley.com. If you indicated that you were interested in receiving offers or information from selected Sitevalley.com sponsors and advertisers, Sitevalley.com will send you email publications and mailings about products and services that we feel may be of interest to you. For those who elect to receive such materials from Sitevalley.com or third parties, and who indicate that they do in their profile, Sitevalley.com will release personal information. Personal information released includes name, email address and other necessary information supplied in Sitevalley.com registration process. If at any time you would like to end your subscription to any email materials, follow either the directions posted at the bottom of the email material, or the directions at the email newsletter company's web site.
            p If you enter a contest on Sitevalley.com, we will use the personal information you provided to contact you in the event you win. All Sitevalley.com contest entry forms provide a way for you to opt-out of any communications that is not related to awarding prizes for the promotion. These entry forms also provide users with a choice on whether to receive email marketing materials from third parties. Any information you provide will not be shared with such third parties unless you agree through the appropriate consent box on the entry form. If you enter a contest, you may be asked, under the rules of the promotion, to agree that the promotion sponsor may use your name in relation to announcing and promoting the winners of the promotion. Sitevalley.com may also use personal information if it has reasonable grounds to believe the information could be useful when investigating a contravention of a federal, provincial or foreign law; for an emergency that threatens an individual's life, health or security; if the use is clearly in the individual's interest and consent is not available in a timely way; or if knowledge and consent would compromise the availability or accuracy of the information and collection is required to investigate a breach of an agreement or contravention of a federal or provincial law. Sitevalley.com may disclose personal information: (i) to a lawyer who is representing it; (ii) if required to comply with a subpoena or warrant issued or an order made by a court, person or body with jurisdiction to compel the production of information, or to comply with rules of court relating to the production of records; (iii) to a government institution or part of a government institution that has made a request for the information, identified its lawful authority to obtain the information and indicated that: (A) it suspects that the information relates to national security, the defence of The USA or the conduct of international affairs, (B) the disclosure is requested for the purpose of enforcing any law of The USA, a state or a foreign jurisdiction, carrying out an investigation relating to the enforcement of any such law or gathering intelligence for the purpose of enforcing any such law, or (C) the disclosure is requested for the purpose of administering any law of The USA or a state; (iv) to a person who needs the information because of an emergency that threatens the life, health or security of an individual; (v) for purposes related to investigating a breach of an agreement or a contravention of the laws of The USA or a state; or (vi) where otherwise required by law. Does Sitevalley.com share the information that is collected

            p In order to provide you with content and services that match your interests, Sitevalley.com may have relationships with services and other companies on the Internet. These also may require registration to make them function properly. You can recognize most of these sites by the joint branding of Sitevalley.com and such companies. As well, if you see a logo on the page that says "Powered by third party", you are on a co-branded site. Other third-party relationships are "private label" relationships where another entity provides Sitevalley.com with technology, services and/or content under Sitevalley.com branding. These sites form part of Sitevalley.com if pages at the site display Sitevalley.com branding bar and a link to the Terms and Conditions or to this Privacy Policy. If you provide, or if Sitevalley.com collects, personal information on a co-branded or private label site that forms part of Sitevalley.com, that data may be shared with the partners for the purpose of providing the products and services available at the site.

        .policy__block#policy5
            .fz-h3 Messages about payments and services

            p Sitevalley.com sends you the information about your services and their payments. You can opt out of receiving such messages only if you stop using our services.

        .policy__block#policy6
            .fz-h3 User rights in regards to personal data
            p You are responsible for the security of your Sitevalley.com login ID and password. Please take care when using and storing them. Sitevalley.com recommends that you do not divulge your password to anyone. You should log out of your browser at the end of each computer session to ensure that others cannot access your personal information and correspondence, especially if you share a computer with someone else or are using a computer in a public place like a library or Internet cafe.

        .policy__block#policy10
            .fz-h3 Storing data
            p Please note that Sitevalley.com's sites may contain links to other sites. We cannot and do not represent or guarantee that their privacy practices will be the same as those set out in our Privacy Policy. So bear in mind that sites that are linked to Sitevalley.com sites may have privacy policies which differ from that of Sitevalley.com.

        .policy__block#policy11
            .fz-h3 Policy updates
            p Also, be aware that Sitevalley.com sponsors and other advertisers have links on our sites that take you to other sites that may collect personal information about you. This Privacy Policy does not cover third party data collection practices and Sitevalley.com does not assume any responsibility for the actions of such third parties.


        .policy__block#policy12
            .fz-h3 Contacts
            p Please send your requests to management@Sitevalley.com regarding any questions about Privacy Policy and fulfillment of personal data rights.